WEBVTT

00:01.531 --> 00:05.204
<i>In 2166, an immortal
tyrant named Vandal Savage</i>

00:05.206 --> 00:07.946
<i>conquered the world and
murdered my wife and child.</i>

00:07.948 --> 00:10.621
<i>I have assembled an elite team
to hunt him throughout time</i>

00:10.623 --> 00:12.393
<i>and stop his rise to power.</i>

00:12.395 --> 00:14.151
<i>Unfortunately, my plan is opposed</i>

00:14.153 --> 00:16.520
<i>by the body I'd sworn
my allegiance to:</i>

00:16.522 --> 00:18.002
<i>the Time Masters.</i>

00:18.004 --> 00:20.246
<i>In the future, my friends
may not be heroes,</i>

00:20.248 --> 00:22.211
<i>but if we succeed,</i>

00:22.213 --> 00:25.028
<i>they will be remembered as legends.</i>

00:25.030 --> 00:27.233
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:27.235 --> 00:29.134
<i>Previously on "Legends
of Tomorrow"...</i>

00:29.136 --> 00:31.668
Ray! Ray, I need you! Please!

00:31.670 --> 00:33.022
<i>I thought you were dead.</i>

00:33.024 --> 00:34.767
Well, not only did you
fail to capture Savage.

00:34.769 --> 00:37.240
You also exposed yourselves
and your powers to him,

00:37.242 --> 00:38.708
giving away the element of surprise

00:38.710 --> 00:39.847
for now and all time.

00:39.849 --> 00:41.813
I let you go, you'll deliver the Waverider.

00:41.815 --> 00:43.613
Boys, ship's all yours.

00:43.615 --> 00:45.483
<i>You're a liability to the team.</i>

00:45.485 --> 00:48.251
Only one of us is
walking out of here alive.

00:48.253 --> 00:50.718
[whooshing]

00:50.720 --> 00:53.508
<i>♪ One, two, three o'clock,
four o'clock rock ♪</i>

00:53.510 --> 00:56.092
<i>♪ Five, six, seven o'clock,
eight o'clock rock ♪</i>

00:56.094 --> 00:57.081
<i>♪ Nine, ten, eleven o'clock ♪</i>

00:57.083 --> 00:59.018
Tommy, promise me you won't go too fast.

00:59.020 --> 01:00.764
You got to hold on to something, honey.

01:00.766 --> 01:02.921
- Preferably me.
- Remember.

01:02.923 --> 01:04.367
Just 'cause you stole your grandma's wheels

01:04.369 --> 01:05.659
don't mean you got to drive like her.

01:05.661 --> 01:07.003
You run your mouth pretty fast.

01:07.005 --> 01:09.072
Let's see if your car can keep up.

01:09.074 --> 01:12.427
[engines revving]

01:12.429 --> 01:14.711
- Whoo!
- Let's go!

01:14.713 --> 01:16.313
- [laughter]
- Whoo!

01:16.315 --> 01:24.621
<i>♪
♪</i>

01:31.263 --> 01:34.193
[tire pops]

01:34.195 --> 01:35.432
Tommy, watch it!

01:35.434 --> 01:36.933
[screams]

01:38.570 --> 01:40.237
[crash]

01:40.239 --> 01:41.733
<i>♪ When it's eight,
nine, ten, eleven too ♪</i>

01:41.735 --> 01:44.373
<i>♪ I'll be going strong
and so will you ♪</i>

01:44.375 --> 01:47.033
<i>♪ We're gonna rock around
the clock tonight ♪</i>

01:47.035 --> 01:49.690
<i>♪ We're gonna rock, rock,
rock till broad daylight ♪</i>

01:49.692 --> 01:51.047
<i>♪ We're gonna rock, gonna rock ♪</i>

01:51.049 --> 01:54.818
<i>♪ Around the clock tonight ♪</i>

01:54.820 --> 01:56.188
Yo, James Dean!

01:56.190 --> 01:58.455
Are you...

02:00.667 --> 02:02.968
What's that?

02:04.795 --> 02:07.815
I think that's a comet or something.

02:07.817 --> 02:10.100
It's a meteorite,

02:10.102 --> 02:12.235
in point of fact.

02:12.237 --> 02:16.072
I was drawn to it as well.

02:16.074 --> 02:20.110
Your presence out here was unexpected.

02:20.112 --> 02:23.891
Or perhaps that's just another word for...

02:23.893 --> 02:27.250
destiny.

02:27.252 --> 02:30.186
<i>[exciting music]</i>

02:30.188 --> 02:32.522
<i>♪
♪</i>

02:38.463 --> 02:40.697
I'm not the only one whose vision is blurry

02:40.699 --> 02:41.969
in their left eye, am I?

02:41.971 --> 02:43.759
- Oh.
- Seeing three of everything?

02:43.761 --> 02:44.768
That's normal, right?

02:44.770 --> 02:46.202
Yes, as I mentioned before,

02:46.204 --> 02:47.737
the effect of time travel on the human body

02:47.739 --> 02:50.175
increases with the length of each jaunt.

02:50.177 --> 02:51.322
So where are we?

02:51.324 --> 02:52.776
Harmony Falls, Oregon.

02:52.778 --> 02:54.644
According to Captain Baxter's intel,

02:54.646 --> 02:57.981
Savage makes an appearance
in this quaint little hamlet.

02:57.983 --> 03:01.718
What the hell is Savage
doing in Pleasantville?

03:01.720 --> 03:04.354
Murder, apparently.

03:04.356 --> 03:05.956
Several denizens of Harmony Falls

03:05.958 --> 03:07.223
have been brutally slain,

03:07.225 --> 03:08.758
and others have gone missing.

03:08.760 --> 03:10.794
Huh. Kind of like Rory.

03:10.796 --> 03:12.429
Reports are vague, but it seems like

03:12.431 --> 03:14.564
the killer is an expert with knives.

03:14.566 --> 03:16.536
That sounds like Savage's MO.

03:16.538 --> 03:18.134
Yeah, but serial killing isn't.

03:18.136 --> 03:19.569
Sounds pretty small-time for a guy

03:19.571 --> 03:20.738
who's had coffee with Hitler.

03:20.740 --> 03:22.307
Yeah, well, clearly we
have to assume that Savage

03:22.309 --> 03:24.207
has a larger, more nefarious plan.

03:24.209 --> 03:25.742
But since we've jumped back in time,

03:25.744 --> 03:27.744
Savage isn't expecting us here.

03:27.746 --> 03:29.913
Savage is pretty good at hiding,

03:29.915 --> 03:31.281
even in a small town,

03:31.283 --> 03:33.049
so how do you plan to find him?

03:33.051 --> 03:35.051
By investigating these murders.

03:35.053 --> 03:37.120
Now, there has to be a common link

03:37.122 --> 03:38.588
between the victims,

03:38.590 --> 03:40.690
starting with the first.

03:40.692 --> 03:43.393
<i>A piano teacher was
found slain in her home,</i>

03:43.395 --> 03:44.794
<i>which is now on the market.</i>

03:44.796 --> 03:47.063
There is, of course, crown molding.

03:47.065 --> 03:48.999
All original floors.

03:49.001 --> 03:50.633
Stucco ceiling.

03:50.635 --> 03:52.902
There's a small room above the garage,

03:52.904 --> 03:55.071
suitable for live-in help.

03:55.073 --> 03:57.440
Oh, well, we don't need a maid.

03:57.442 --> 04:01.177
My husband and I get
along just fine on our own.

04:01.179 --> 04:04.114
You know, I have a lovely Tudor style

04:04.116 --> 04:05.582
in another town.

04:05.584 --> 04:08.218
A more... accepting one.

04:08.220 --> 04:10.920
Forward-thinking.

04:10.922 --> 04:13.223
No, that's... that's fine.

04:13.225 --> 04:16.726
I like my towns backward.

04:16.728 --> 04:18.628
<i>Dr. Matt Miller was found murdered</i>

04:18.630 --> 04:20.815
<i>on the grounds of the
asylum where he worked.</i>

04:20.817 --> 04:23.099
<i>The sanitarium is in
need of a replacement.</i>

04:23.101 --> 04:26.669
It's a very impressive facility.

04:26.671 --> 04:29.472
I did my doctoral
thesis on socio-pathology

04:29.474 --> 04:31.781
in relationship to serial murder, actually.

04:31.783 --> 04:33.478
Well, that'll certainly
come in handy around here.

04:33.480 --> 04:35.298
We've been short-staffed ever since

04:35.300 --> 04:38.080
Dr. Miller's sudden demise.

04:38.082 --> 04:39.315
Of course, I could never consider

04:39.317 --> 04:40.750
accepting a position here

04:40.752 --> 04:44.254
without my faithful nurse/assistant.

04:44.256 --> 04:45.722
Yes, well,

04:45.724 --> 04:48.324
she looks like she'll fit right in.

04:48.326 --> 04:50.994
[chuckles]

04:50.996 --> 04:53.129
Meanwhile, Jefferson is the perfect age

04:53.131 --> 04:54.931
to discern the facts
behind the disappearance

04:54.933 --> 04:56.900
of three teenagers who went missing

04:56.902 --> 04:59.035
a week before these murders began.

04:59.037 --> 05:01.337
So Raymond and Kendra are shacking up,

05:01.339 --> 05:03.073
Sara's Nurse Ratched,

05:03.075 --> 05:05.241
and Jax's the new kid in town.

05:05.243 --> 05:08.044
Where does that leave me?

05:08.046 --> 05:10.980
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

05:10.982 --> 05:17.143
<i>♪
♪</i>

05:17.145 --> 05:18.906
We're looking for the sheriff.

05:18.908 --> 05:20.256
Well, you found him.

05:20.258 --> 05:21.889
Bud Ellison.

05:21.891 --> 05:23.860
How can I help you, folks?

05:23.862 --> 05:25.654
Special Agent Rip Hunter.

05:25.656 --> 05:28.031
This is my partner, Leonard.

05:28.033 --> 05:30.777
We are here to investigate
the serial murders

05:30.779 --> 05:33.670
which have plagued this
sleepy old town of yours.

05:33.672 --> 05:35.845
Whoa. Now, slow down there, buddy.

05:35.847 --> 05:38.427
There ain't no serial killer anywhere.

05:38.429 --> 05:40.777
All we got is some
unexplained accidents is all.

05:40.779 --> 05:42.375
How about you hand over those case files

05:42.377 --> 05:45.113
so we can decide for ourselves?

05:45.115 --> 05:47.517
Or we can come back with a court order

05:47.519 --> 05:50.887
and a really nasty disposition.

05:52.457 --> 05:55.992
Anything for our friends at the bureau.

05:58.911 --> 06:00.563
Nice work, partner.

06:00.565 --> 06:02.475
You're not my partner.

06:02.477 --> 06:06.275
There's only one person I
ever trusted on this job,

06:06.277 --> 06:08.771
and we all know how that turned out.

06:08.773 --> 06:11.508
<i>['50s rock music playing]</i>

06:11.510 --> 06:13.243
Schwinn Hornets.

06:13.245 --> 06:15.501
I had the very same one
when I was their age.

06:15.503 --> 06:17.247
Seeing white picket fences

06:17.249 --> 06:19.716
and perfect family houses,

06:19.718 --> 06:21.885
it's enough to make one nostalgic.

06:21.887 --> 06:23.153
Or nauseated.

06:23.155 --> 06:25.048
Oh, come on, Ms. Lance.

06:25.050 --> 06:26.456
Even someone as jaded as yourself

06:26.458 --> 06:29.926
can't deny how idyllic this time was.

06:29.928 --> 06:31.427
Yeah.

06:31.429 --> 06:32.629
If you're white.

06:32.631 --> 06:33.997
And a man.

06:33.999 --> 06:35.698
And straight. And...

06:35.700 --> 06:37.446
Okay, okay. I get the point.

06:37.448 --> 06:38.783
Dude, even if this town

06:38.785 --> 06:40.527
wasn't full of small-minded idiots,

06:40.529 --> 06:42.672
it'd still be creepy as hell.

06:42.674 --> 06:45.041
I used to watch all these
old horror movies with my mom,

06:45.043 --> 06:47.877
and they all started
off in places like this.

06:47.879 --> 06:50.079
See, first it's all perfect,

06:50.081 --> 06:52.081
and then, boom, some
alien monster beast thing

06:52.083 --> 06:53.583
starts killing kids on Lovers' Lane.

06:53.585 --> 06:56.286
- Ooh.
- I'm telling you, man.

06:58.538 --> 07:00.534
What is it?

07:00.536 --> 07:02.458
An unhappy cheerleader.

07:02.460 --> 07:04.093
Now, that is scary.

07:04.095 --> 07:05.809
That girl was from the newspaper articles

07:05.811 --> 07:07.060
Rip showed us.

07:07.062 --> 07:08.565
She knows the guys that went missing.

07:08.567 --> 07:12.168
Perhaps she can illuminate
us as to their whereabouts.

07:12.170 --> 07:13.937
Dude, can you not just say,

07:13.939 --> 07:15.715
"Hey, Jax, why don't you go talk to her

07:15.717 --> 07:17.167
and find out what she knows?"

07:17.169 --> 07:18.575
Like a normal person.

07:18.577 --> 07:19.776
Hey, Jax,

07:19.778 --> 07:21.711
why don't you just go do that?

07:21.713 --> 07:23.489
All right. We mustn't dawdle.

07:23.491 --> 07:26.149
I believe our lunch
hour is nearly at an end.

07:26.151 --> 07:28.618
Come along, Nurse.

07:28.620 --> 07:30.213
Just so you know,

07:30.215 --> 07:33.382
Ra's al Ghul taught me
how to kill someone slowly,

07:33.384 --> 07:37.060
over the course of days.

07:37.062 --> 07:42.423
<i>♪
♪</i>

07:42.425 --> 07:45.130
Hey, you mind if I sit?

07:45.132 --> 07:46.433
[gasps] You can't sit with him.

07:46.435 --> 07:49.234
What is up with them?

07:50.442 --> 07:52.542
Um...

07:52.544 --> 07:54.462
I-I don't think they've seen anyone...

07:54.464 --> 07:58.147
Dip their fries in their milk shake before?

07:58.149 --> 07:59.591
Oh.

07:59.593 --> 08:00.850
Mm-mm, don't knock it
till you tried it, girl.

08:00.852 --> 08:03.519
No.

08:03.521 --> 08:06.022
Okay.

08:10.018 --> 08:11.540
- Okay, that's really good.
- Right?

08:11.542 --> 08:12.962
Yeah.

08:12.964 --> 08:15.622
- I'm Jax.
- Betty.

08:15.624 --> 08:17.325
Nice to meet you, Betty.

08:17.327 --> 08:18.968
Hey, Betty.

08:18.970 --> 08:21.437
Just because your boyfriend went AWOL

08:21.439 --> 08:24.974
doesn't mean you have to
slum it with this loser.

08:24.976 --> 08:27.476
Why don't you do yourself a favor, Biff?

08:27.478 --> 08:29.912
Keep walking before you really,

08:29.914 --> 08:32.381
really embarrass yourself.

08:32.384 --> 08:34.484
[slurps]

08:37.385 --> 08:40.390
What? You want to take a swing at me?

08:43.061 --> 08:46.229
Hey. Let's go.

08:46.231 --> 08:48.831
This isn't over.

08:48.833 --> 08:50.122
[scoffs]

08:50.124 --> 08:52.326
I am so sorry about that.

08:52.328 --> 08:56.072
- Uh, where were we?
- No, that was amazing.

08:56.074 --> 08:58.207
[chuckles]

08:59.978 --> 09:02.278
Do you want to hang out tomorrow night?

09:02.280 --> 09:03.646
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

09:03.648 --> 09:05.682
- It's a date.
- Okay.

09:05.684 --> 09:07.653
<i>[slow music playing]</i>

09:07.655 --> 09:11.135
<i>♪ I was caught by your kisses ♪</i>

09:11.137 --> 09:12.996
Well, now that we're done moving in,

09:12.998 --> 09:15.591
care to dance?

09:15.593 --> 09:17.160
Sure.

09:17.162 --> 09:18.810
<i>♪ Locked in your arms ♪</i>

09:18.812 --> 09:20.613
<i>♪ There's no mistake ♪</i>

09:20.615 --> 09:23.013
So yesterday we kissed,

09:23.015 --> 09:25.579
and now today we're married.

09:25.581 --> 09:26.995
Okay, I know it seems
like we're moving fast,

09:26.997 --> 09:28.604
but this is all pretend.

09:28.606 --> 09:31.002
Soon as we get a divorce,

09:31.004 --> 09:32.650
we'll figure us out.

09:32.652 --> 09:34.877
In the meantime,

09:34.879 --> 09:36.843
doesn't mean we can't have fun with it.

09:36.845 --> 09:38.755
[giggles]

09:38.757 --> 09:40.249
This is a waste of time.

09:40.251 --> 09:41.751
We should be out there looking for Savage,

09:41.753 --> 09:43.585
not playing doctor.

09:43.587 --> 09:44.554
You know what I mean.

09:44.556 --> 09:45.688
I'd like to think

09:45.690 --> 09:47.156
that in a town with multiple murders

09:47.158 --> 09:48.791
and missing teenagers,

09:48.793 --> 09:50.393
the local insane asylum

09:50.395 --> 09:52.261
would be fertile ground for clues.

09:52.263 --> 09:53.763
Let's start by reviewing the files

09:53.765 --> 09:57.255
of every inmate with a history of violence.

09:57.257 --> 10:02.305
If you wouldn't mind getting
me those files, Nurse?

10:02.307 --> 10:05.575
Literally for days.

10:05.577 --> 10:08.511
<i>[mischievous music]</i>

10:08.513 --> 10:10.146
<i>♪
♪</i>

10:18.563 --> 10:20.723
Is that a new perfume I smell?

10:20.725 --> 10:22.535
You know, if you're trying
to drive everyone crazy,

10:22.537 --> 10:24.794
I have to tell you, it's working.

10:24.796 --> 10:26.162
I'm very busy right now.

10:26.164 --> 10:27.563
You know what your problem is?

10:27.565 --> 10:29.913
You don't know how to have a good time.

10:29.915 --> 10:31.178
Now, what you need

10:31.180 --> 10:34.003
is a man who can show you one.

10:34.005 --> 10:37.206
- [grunts]
- Oops.

10:37.208 --> 10:38.674
[groans]

10:38.676 --> 10:41.910
[laughs]

10:41.912 --> 10:43.609
Thank you.

10:43.611 --> 10:45.348
That was incredible.

10:45.350 --> 10:46.482
Well, maybe next time,

10:46.484 --> 10:48.698
he'll take no for an answer.

10:48.700 --> 10:52.655
Uh, it's not just him.

10:52.657 --> 10:54.910
Most of the doctors here
are looking for a good time,

10:54.912 --> 10:57.059
and most of the nurses all say yes,

10:57.061 --> 10:59.128
'cause they're looking to get married.

10:59.130 --> 11:01.864
Oh. Not you, though.

11:01.866 --> 11:03.229
I'm...

11:03.231 --> 11:06.634
not really looking for a husband.

11:06.636 --> 11:08.664
Today's my first day.

11:08.666 --> 11:12.008
Care to give the new girl a tour?

11:14.779 --> 11:17.547
The files you asked for, Doctor.

11:17.549 --> 11:19.432
Excellent, Nurse.

11:19.434 --> 11:21.717
I could also go for a cup of coffee.

11:21.719 --> 11:22.907
Me too.

11:22.909 --> 11:26.161
Black. Two sugars.

11:26.163 --> 11:27.380
[giggles]

11:27.382 --> 11:28.839
And the cafeteria's over there.

11:28.841 --> 11:30.938
It's better than what we serve the patients

11:30.940 --> 11:31.901
but not by much.

11:31.903 --> 11:34.230
- Mmm.
- Oh.

11:34.232 --> 11:36.065
What's down there?

11:36.067 --> 11:37.667
Oh, that's Hall H,

11:37.669 --> 11:39.304
the restricted ward.

11:39.306 --> 11:41.404
It's for Dr. Knox's patients.

11:41.406 --> 11:43.906
Violent psychotics.

11:43.908 --> 11:47.109
That part of the tour is worth skipping.

11:47.111 --> 11:49.605
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

11:49.607 --> 11:50.614
[doorbell rings]

11:50.616 --> 11:52.181
Coming!

11:52.183 --> 11:54.632
I'm coming.

11:54.634 --> 11:56.487
Welcome to the neighborhood. [laughs]

11:56.489 --> 11:57.393
Thank you.

11:57.395 --> 12:00.240
Thank you so much, Miss...

12:00.242 --> 12:02.124
Mrs. Knox.

12:02.126 --> 12:03.509
Gail Knox, and this

12:03.511 --> 12:06.062
is my husband, Curtis.

12:06.064 --> 12:07.630
Lovely to meet you.

12:07.632 --> 12:10.566
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

12:10.568 --> 12:13.035
<i>♪
♪</i>

12:20.612 --> 12:23.746
[wind whooshing]

12:29.537 --> 12:31.636
[wings flapping]

12:31.638 --> 12:32.747
[screeching]

12:32.749 --> 12:36.259
[screaming]

12:40.164 --> 12:43.366
<i>[wings flapping]</i>

12:49.134 --> 12:50.519
I'm sorry, have...

12:50.521 --> 12:51.656
have we met before?

12:51.658 --> 12:53.206
I-I doubt it.

12:53.208 --> 12:55.966
I... we just moved in

12:55.968 --> 12:57.977
from way out of town.

12:57.979 --> 12:59.737
I hope you like tuna surprise.

12:59.739 --> 13:01.505
Are you kidding? I love tuna surpri...

13:01.507 --> 13:03.340
- Oh, my God...
- Raymond!

13:03.342 --> 13:05.784
These are our new neighbors,

13:05.786 --> 13:07.866
Curtis and Gail.

13:07.868 --> 13:09.847
What a surprise.

13:09.849 --> 13:12.550
Tuna surprise. So many surprises.

13:12.552 --> 13:14.518
Well, another reason why we dropped by

13:14.520 --> 13:16.954
was to let you know that we
are having a soiree tonight.

13:16.956 --> 13:18.322
Stop by anytime after 8:00.

13:18.324 --> 13:19.490
We're just across the street.

13:19.492 --> 13:20.624
Don't bother to ring the bell.

13:20.626 --> 13:23.427
No, you just walk right on in.

13:23.429 --> 13:25.596
It's that kind of neighborhood.

13:25.598 --> 13:27.898
Savage doesn't think I recognize him,

13:27.900 --> 13:29.900
which means he won't try to kill me.

13:29.902 --> 13:32.536
He can't steal my powers
before I've found them.

13:32.538 --> 13:33.837
Don't forget, we also have to figure out

13:33.839 --> 13:35.172
why he's killing the townsfolk.

13:35.174 --> 13:36.707
Are you really eating that?

13:36.709 --> 13:38.209
Say what you want about Savage.

13:38.211 --> 13:39.677
He makes one hell of a casserole.

13:39.679 --> 13:40.945
Yes, well, Mr. Snart and I

13:40.947 --> 13:43.581
have been analyzing these forensic files.

13:43.583 --> 13:45.416
Which reveal nothing except

13:45.418 --> 13:47.051
Savage is very good

13:47.053 --> 13:48.953
at making people disappear.

13:48.955 --> 13:51.255
Hmm, something you both have in common.

13:51.257 --> 13:53.591
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:53.593 --> 13:56.260
Are we just gonna pretend
like none of this happened?

13:56.262 --> 13:58.762
That Mick Rory wasn't a part of our team?

13:58.764 --> 14:00.931
If you can just ice your
best friend like that,

14:00.933 --> 14:02.566
I hate to think what you could do to us.

14:02.568 --> 14:05.035
Right now, we need to stay
focused on the mission.

14:05.037 --> 14:06.203
Look, Savage is going to be busy

14:06.205 --> 14:08.272
with this little cocktail party.

14:08.274 --> 14:09.807
Whilst you two keep an eye on him,

14:09.809 --> 14:11.275
Sara and Martin have the opportunity

14:11.277 --> 14:12.476
to find out what he's doing

14:12.478 --> 14:14.278
in the secret wing of that asylum.

14:14.280 --> 14:21.151
<i>♪
♪</i>

14:21.153 --> 14:23.120
If you're looking for booze,

14:23.122 --> 14:24.822
you're in the wrong office.

14:24.824 --> 14:26.890
Dr. Knox doesn't drink.

14:26.892 --> 14:31.428
But I know where Dr.
Enbom keeps the good stuff.

14:31.430 --> 14:33.464
<i>♪ Bop-bop-bop,
bop-ba-dop-bop ♪</i>

14:33.466 --> 14:36.333
<i>♪ It seems like
everyone's in love ♪</i>

14:36.335 --> 14:38.469
<i>♪ Everyone but me ♪</i>

14:38.471 --> 14:40.938
<i>♪ I can't find a doggone soul ♪</i>

14:40.940 --> 14:43.215
<i>♪ To share my company ♪</i>

14:43.217 --> 14:44.808
Oh, there you are, dear.

14:44.810 --> 14:47.478
I could go for another glass of bubbly.

14:47.480 --> 14:51.181
Then I suggest you find a waitress.

14:51.183 --> 14:52.583
Well, I-I just assumed...

14:52.585 --> 14:54.099
You assumed wrong.

14:54.101 --> 14:58.355
So why don't you go ahead
and get your own champagne?

14:58.357 --> 15:00.442
Wow, I guess this whole

15:00.444 --> 15:03.327
interracial marriage
thing really is a novelty.

15:03.329 --> 15:05.562
Well, go ahead and let them stare.

15:05.564 --> 15:07.742
I've got the most beautiful
woman in the room on my arm.

15:07.744 --> 15:10.100
I couldn't agree with you more.

15:10.102 --> 15:11.769
Oh, hello.

15:11.771 --> 15:13.304
Uh, thank you for inviting us.

15:13.306 --> 15:16.206
Your home, is, um, very...

15:16.208 --> 15:17.841
normal.

15:17.843 --> 15:21.111
Oh, we are just glad that you could attend.

15:21.113 --> 15:23.380
Let me fix you a drink.

15:25.662 --> 15:27.229
Okay, we need to split up.

15:27.231 --> 15:28.440
You check the back rooms,

15:28.442 --> 15:30.698
and I'll see what I can find up here.

15:30.700 --> 15:32.489
Uh, you sure that's a good idea?

15:32.491 --> 15:33.751
Leaving you up here by yourself

15:33.753 --> 15:36.974
with Savage?

15:36.976 --> 15:38.571
I'm pretty sure he's not gonna kill me

15:38.573 --> 15:41.665
next to the canapés, Ray.

15:41.667 --> 15:42.701
Go.

15:42.703 --> 15:44.101
I'll let you know if I need help.

15:44.103 --> 15:48.625
<i>♪ Fall in love with me ♪</i>

15:48.627 --> 15:50.462
[sighs] You've been so many places.

15:50.464 --> 15:52.851
It's like you've had three lives.

15:52.853 --> 15:56.246
Me, I've never left Harmony Falls.

15:56.248 --> 15:57.981
That's your first mistake.

15:57.983 --> 15:59.450
This town sucks.

15:59.452 --> 16:02.686
Wow, you do not hold back.

16:02.688 --> 16:06.056
I've learned life's too short.

16:06.058 --> 16:08.425
So you have a girlfriend?

16:08.427 --> 16:09.793
I just mean,

16:09.795 --> 16:13.163
seems pretty obvious you're not into guys.

16:13.165 --> 16:15.466
Uh, I, uh...

16:15.468 --> 16:17.468
I don't know what you're talking about.

16:17.470 --> 16:18.920
Okay.

16:18.922 --> 16:21.839
We don't have to talk about
it if you don't want to.

16:21.841 --> 16:25.876
But just so you know,

16:25.878 --> 16:28.479
I'm really good at keeping secrets.

16:28.481 --> 16:31.415
<i>[soft music]</i>

16:31.417 --> 16:32.883
<i>♪
♪</i>

16:32.885 --> 16:35.552
Funny you should say that.

16:35.554 --> 16:37.630
I did

16:37.632 --> 16:40.824
kiss a girl once.

16:40.826 --> 16:43.927
I didn't think that made me a...

16:43.929 --> 16:47.631
- You know.
- A lesbian?

16:47.633 --> 16:48.517
What?

16:48.519 --> 16:51.702
It's not a bad word.

16:51.704 --> 16:55.205
Well, it is around here.

16:55.207 --> 16:56.433
[sighs]

16:56.435 --> 17:00.244
Well, good thing I'm not from around here.

17:02.481 --> 17:04.181
[clears throat] Uh, Nurse Lance,

17:04.183 --> 17:06.349
may I have a word with you, please?

17:10.423 --> 17:11.954
Well, now I see what's been going on.

17:11.957 --> 17:13.290
While I've been busy working,

17:13.291 --> 17:15.291
you were busy seducing that young woman.

17:15.294 --> 17:18.328
Actually, I was liberating her.

17:18.329 --> 17:19.938
With an option to seduce her later.

17:19.940 --> 17:20.897
Then what?

17:20.900 --> 17:22.465
This poor young woman

17:22.468 --> 17:25.068
will have to remain in the
sexually repressive 1950s

17:25.069 --> 17:26.940
long after you've returned to a timeship

17:26.942 --> 17:28.672
and disappeared from her life forever.

17:28.674 --> 17:29.656
You know what, Doc?

17:29.658 --> 17:31.074
I would love for someone

17:31.076 --> 17:32.509
to drop into my life and tell me

17:32.511 --> 17:34.812
that the future's gonna be a better place.

17:34.814 --> 17:36.738
[bell ringing]

17:36.740 --> 17:38.849
Get to Hall H!

17:38.851 --> 17:41.752
<i>[ominous music]</i>

17:41.754 --> 17:42.793
<i>♪
♪</i>

17:42.795 --> 17:44.354
Your husband must be a fool

17:44.356 --> 17:46.223
to leave a woman such as yourself

17:46.225 --> 17:48.859
alone at a party.

17:48.861 --> 17:51.528
He doesn't seem like your type.

17:51.530 --> 17:53.397
That's a rather interesting thing to say.

17:53.399 --> 17:56.900
You hardly know me.

17:56.902 --> 18:00.170
And yet I feel like I do.

18:00.172 --> 18:03.640
Let me ask you a question, Kendra.

18:03.642 --> 18:06.143
Do you believe in past lives?

18:06.145 --> 18:09.079
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

18:09.081 --> 18:17.354
<i>♪
♪</i>

18:19.369 --> 18:21.625
Do you believe in fate?

18:21.627 --> 18:24.194
Fate is a prison.

18:24.196 --> 18:27.739
When free will is gone, what's left?

18:27.741 --> 18:30.300
Destiny.

18:30.302 --> 18:31.209
[phone rings]

18:31.211 --> 18:33.370
Oh.

18:37.580 --> 18:39.778
Hello.

18:39.780 --> 18:41.504
Yeah. I understand.

18:41.506 --> 18:45.115
Of course. I'm on my way.

18:45.117 --> 18:48.099
Looks like we have to
finish our discussion later.

18:48.101 --> 18:51.655
One of my patients needs attention.

18:51.657 --> 18:54.758
Enjoy the party.

18:56.495 --> 18:58.295
[sighs]

18:58.297 --> 19:01.231
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:01.233 --> 19:09.506
<i>♪
♪</i>

19:11.176 --> 19:12.513
Tommy, Tommy, Tommy.

19:12.515 --> 19:14.678
I-I thought the two of us

19:14.680 --> 19:16.780
had an understanding.

19:16.782 --> 19:18.482
I've allowed you and your cohorts

19:18.484 --> 19:20.651
the occasional freedom to run free

19:20.653 --> 19:23.950
and to feed your thirst, and then...

19:23.952 --> 19:26.189
then you do something like this.

19:26.191 --> 19:29.092
[snarling]

19:29.094 --> 19:34.398
<i>♪
♪</i>

19:38.260 --> 19:39.261
I'm sorry, Mr. Palmer.

19:39.263 --> 19:42.669
I'm unfamiliar with the term "man cave."

19:42.671 --> 19:43.978
Oh, it's a room in a basement

19:43.980 --> 19:45.279
where a dude goes to be alone

19:45.281 --> 19:46.490
or watch football.

19:46.492 --> 19:48.916
In Savage's case, it's kill people.

19:48.918 --> 19:51.085
So Ray and I break in and find out

19:51.087 --> 19:53.187
what Savage is doing in Harmony Falls.

19:55.625 --> 19:57.458
- Ho, ho, ho!
- Ooh.

19:57.460 --> 19:59.326
Is tonight the Enchantment
Under the Sea dance?

19:59.328 --> 20:00.961
[chuckles] I got a date tonight

20:00.963 --> 20:03.130
with Tommy Fuller's cheerleader girlfriend.

20:03.132 --> 20:04.498
Turns out Betty's boyfriend

20:04.500 --> 20:06.400
was one of the missing high school kids.

20:06.402 --> 20:08.269
I think she knows more
than she's letting on.

20:08.271 --> 20:09.904
Mm, she's also a white girl

20:09.906 --> 20:13.007
in a very, uh, unenlightened community.

20:13.009 --> 20:14.975
So please, be careful

20:14.977 --> 20:16.343
when you're out in public with her.

20:16.345 --> 20:18.746
An immortal psychopath and racists.

20:18.748 --> 20:20.347
I'm beginning to like
this quaint little town

20:20.349 --> 20:21.282
less and less.

20:21.284 --> 20:24.218
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

20:24.220 --> 20:26.487
<i>♪
♪</i>

20:26.489 --> 20:27.421
[exhales deeply]

20:27.423 --> 20:33.060
<i>♪
♪</i>

20:33.062 --> 20:34.595
<i>How's it going over there?</i>

20:34.597 --> 20:37.498
I'm in.

20:37.500 --> 20:39.767
What do you see?

20:39.769 --> 20:41.144
Uh...

20:41.146 --> 20:43.696
nothing all that hideous.

20:43.698 --> 20:47.611
Except for a terrible
collection of golf pants.

20:47.613 --> 20:50.144
Hang on.

20:50.146 --> 20:53.080
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

20:53.082 --> 20:57.705
<i>♪
♪</i>

20:57.707 --> 20:59.687
Ray?

20:59.689 --> 21:02.256
Ray, it's Savage. He's back.

21:02.258 --> 21:03.830
<i>Did you hear me, Ray?</i>

21:03.832 --> 21:05.926
<i>You need to get out of there!</i>

21:05.928 --> 21:07.428
I think I found something.

21:07.430 --> 21:09.363
<i>No, no, no, no. You don't have time.</i>

21:09.365 --> 21:10.282
<i>[door clicks open]</i>

21:10.284 --> 21:11.832
<i>He's already inside.</i>

21:11.834 --> 21:20.140
<i>♪
♪</i>

21:22.044 --> 21:24.979
<i>[mischievous music]</i>

21:24.981 --> 21:28.449
<i>♪
♪</i>

21:30.000 --> 21:36.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

21:37.660 --> 21:40.794
Don't you ever get freaked out?

21:40.796 --> 21:43.671
I mean, being in an insane asylum

21:43.673 --> 21:45.165
by yourself

21:45.167 --> 21:46.834
in the middle of the night?

21:46.836 --> 21:49.770
Freaked out? No.

21:49.772 --> 21:52.473
Lonely? Yes.

21:53.843 --> 21:55.376
Actually, there is

21:55.378 --> 21:58.584
one place in the hospital that scares me.

21:58.586 --> 22:01.749
Dr. Knox's restricted wing.

22:01.751 --> 22:05.085
Do you know what he's doing
to the patients down there?

22:05.087 --> 22:06.387
No.

22:06.389 --> 22:08.522
I don't like to think about it.

22:08.524 --> 22:10.491
What do you like to think about?

22:10.493 --> 22:13.427
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

22:13.429 --> 22:20.480
<i>♪
♪</i>

22:20.482 --> 22:21.468
What's wrong?

22:21.470 --> 22:22.936
- Nothing.
- I thought you said...

22:22.938 --> 22:25.039
I-I just... I have to get back to work.

22:25.041 --> 22:27.641
<i>♪
♪</i>

22:27.643 --> 22:30.391
<i>[slow music playing]</i>

22:30.393 --> 22:32.613
You look great tonight.

22:32.615 --> 22:35.096
<i>♪
♪</i>

22:35.098 --> 22:37.064
<i>♪ Don't have to tell me ♪</i>

22:37.066 --> 22:39.787
Mm... whoa. Whoa.

22:39.789 --> 22:42.489
- Uh...
- I'm sorry. I thought that...

22:42.491 --> 22:43.891
No, don't be sorry.

22:43.893 --> 22:45.359
It's just, uh,

22:45.361 --> 22:47.161
I thought girls from 1958

22:47.163 --> 22:49.563
moved a little bit slower.

22:49.565 --> 22:52.039
Girls from 1958?

22:52.041 --> 22:53.967
I mean, uh,

22:53.969 --> 22:55.569
I think we should get to know each other

22:55.571 --> 22:58.639
a little bit better first.

22:58.641 --> 23:00.234
Okay.

23:00.236 --> 23:02.009
What do you want to know?

23:02.011 --> 23:04.845
Those guys back at the soda shop,

23:04.847 --> 23:09.383
they mentioned something about
your boyfriend going AWOL?

23:09.385 --> 23:10.541
Tommy.

23:10.543 --> 23:11.967
What happened to him?

23:11.969 --> 23:14.221
It's kind of a long story.

23:14.223 --> 23:17.424
Well, I got all the time in the world.

23:17.426 --> 23:19.460
We were drag racing down on Route 7

23:19.462 --> 23:21.095
with Davis and Billy

23:21.097 --> 23:23.397
when Tommy's car

23:23.399 --> 23:25.899
went into a ditch.

23:25.901 --> 23:27.067
That's when they found it.

23:27.069 --> 23:28.669
Found what?

23:28.671 --> 23:29.866
This...

23:29.868 --> 23:31.788
Been looking all over for you.

23:31.790 --> 23:32.596
- Get out!
- No!

23:32.598 --> 23:34.274
Get out of the car!

23:34.276 --> 23:37.511
Hey, get the hell off me, man!

23:37.513 --> 23:39.613
Stop it! Stop it!

23:39.615 --> 23:42.549
[shrieking]

23:42.551 --> 23:45.052
both: Ah!

23:45.054 --> 23:47.254
Get in! Get in!

23:47.256 --> 23:49.056
Ah!

23:49.058 --> 23:52.126
Go!

23:52.128 --> 23:54.361
- [snarls]
- [gasps]

23:54.363 --> 23:56.130
Oh, come on!

23:56.132 --> 23:58.499
[shrieking]

23:58.501 --> 24:01.568
Tommy?

24:01.570 --> 24:04.705
[screaming]

24:07.009 --> 24:08.809
[engine turns over]

24:08.811 --> 24:11.078
I am not playing anymore!

24:11.080 --> 24:13.213
[engine revving]

24:13.215 --> 24:15.015
[screeches]

24:15.017 --> 24:17.317
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

24:17.319 --> 24:19.386
Don't worry, Betty. I'm
gonna get you out of here.

24:19.388 --> 24:23.123
<i>♪
♪</i>

24:23.125 --> 24:26.140
[gasping]

24:26.142 --> 24:27.594
Nice driving.

24:27.596 --> 24:30.364
Hang in there. Gideon's gonna fix you.

24:30.366 --> 24:31.598
Who's Gideon?

24:31.600 --> 24:33.770
Uh, a doctor, of sorts.

24:33.772 --> 24:35.035
Okay.

24:35.037 --> 24:39.348
[siren wailing]

24:39.350 --> 24:42.976
You need to pull over, Jax.

24:42.978 --> 24:44.178
[sighs]

24:48.423 --> 24:49.629
Hey.

24:49.631 --> 24:51.852
Relax.

24:51.854 --> 24:53.187
Yeah, 'cause it's not like

24:53.189 --> 24:54.721
I'm a black kid in a small town

24:54.723 --> 24:56.857
with a white girl
bleeding all over my seat.

24:56.859 --> 25:01.295
<i>♪
♪</i>

25:01.297 --> 25:03.764
You were driving to beat
the devil back there.

25:03.766 --> 25:05.632
That explain why your car looks like hell?

25:05.634 --> 25:07.801
I need to get my friend to a hospital.

25:07.803 --> 25:09.303
- Friend?
- Yeah.

25:09.305 --> 25:10.838
And there's more wounded on Lovers' Lane.

25:10.840 --> 25:12.372
Some... some kind of attack.

25:12.374 --> 25:13.507
What were you doing with this girl

25:13.509 --> 25:15.209
on Lovers' Lane, boy?

25:15.211 --> 25:17.177
There are kids back there that
could really use your help,

25:17.179 --> 25:19.179
and she needs medical attention right now.

25:19.181 --> 25:21.181
Put your hands on the car and spread 'em.

25:21.183 --> 25:24.318
Listen, you can play
Boss Hogg all you want,

25:24.320 --> 25:26.353
but I'm not gonna let
that girl bleed to death,

25:26.355 --> 25:28.355
so I tell you what: I'm
gonna get back in my car,

25:28.357 --> 25:30.057
and I'm gonna take her to the hospital.

25:30.059 --> 25:32.559
[grunts]

25:32.561 --> 25:40.834
<i>♪
♪</i>

25:46.191 --> 25:48.593
Gideon traced Jax's last biosignature

25:48.595 --> 25:50.701
to this location.

25:50.703 --> 25:53.638
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

25:53.640 --> 25:55.294
<i>♪
♪</i>

25:55.296 --> 25:57.108
Well, it seems you had good reason

25:57.110 --> 25:59.210
to be concerned for Mr. Jackson's safety.

25:59.212 --> 26:02.713
Yeah, sucks being right all the time.

26:02.715 --> 26:05.416
<i>♪
♪</i>

26:05.418 --> 26:07.852
<i>She has suffered several
severe lacerations.</i>

26:07.854 --> 26:09.820
<i>I am attempting to
cauterize the wound.</i>

26:09.822 --> 26:11.188
- What happened?
- I don't know.

26:11.190 --> 26:12.924
But I'm guessing Jax and Peggy Sue

26:12.926 --> 26:14.759
had a pretty lousy first date.

26:14.761 --> 26:16.130
Where is Jefferson?

26:16.132 --> 26:18.731
There was no sign of him in the car.

26:18.733 --> 26:20.765
These wounds don't appear

26:20.767 --> 26:22.296
consistent with a knife.

26:22.298 --> 26:23.254
<i>Correct.</i>

26:23.256 --> 26:25.937
<i>I believe these lacerations
were made by talons.</i>

26:25.939 --> 26:28.739
It was Tommy.

26:28.741 --> 26:30.575
Tommy Fuller, one of the missing teenagers.

26:30.577 --> 26:31.776
He was like a bird.

26:31.778 --> 26:35.244
He... he was like a bird monster.

26:35.246 --> 26:37.437
<i>Captain, analysis of
Miss Seavers' blood</i>

26:37.439 --> 26:40.885
<i>reveals traces of silicate minerals.</i>

26:40.887 --> 26:43.988
Miss Seavers, do you recall
Tommy coming into contact

26:43.990 --> 26:47.112
with a meteor of some kind?

26:47.114 --> 26:49.093
The car crash...

26:49.095 --> 26:51.062
it was...

26:51.064 --> 26:52.563
it was glowing.

26:52.565 --> 26:54.532
She's talking about an Nth Metal meteorite.

26:54.534 --> 26:56.801
Say something that makes sense.

26:56.803 --> 26:58.803
It seems Mr. Fuller has come into contact

26:58.805 --> 27:01.105
with a meteorite with mutagenic properties.

27:01.107 --> 27:02.440
Try again.

27:02.442 --> 27:03.874
Apparently, Miss Seavers' boyfriend

27:03.876 --> 27:05.561
has been exposed to the same type of meteor

27:05.563 --> 27:08.589
that Kendra came into contact with.

27:08.591 --> 27:09.489
Me?

27:09.491 --> 27:12.116
Well, you and Carter.

27:12.118 --> 27:13.484
4,000 years ago.

27:13.486 --> 27:15.820
The meteorite which gave you your powers

27:15.822 --> 27:17.455
appears to be of the same variety

27:17.457 --> 27:18.756
that mutated Tommy Fuller.

27:18.758 --> 27:21.192
And I'm guessing it's not curable.

27:21.194 --> 27:22.893
Well, I-I suppose,

27:22.895 --> 27:24.795
if the talons which lacerated her

27:24.797 --> 27:26.530
left some mutagenic residue, I could...

27:26.532 --> 27:28.609
Yes or no?

27:28.611 --> 27:29.867
Perhaps.

27:29.869 --> 27:33.537
Why don't you get to work on that, Martin?

27:33.539 --> 27:36.641
Okay, so if Savage isn't
the one doing the killing,

27:36.643 --> 27:38.397
what is he doing in town?

27:38.399 --> 27:41.512
Doesn't matter.

27:41.514 --> 27:42.947
We can take him down.

27:42.949 --> 27:44.482
The Amon Dagger. Where did you...

27:44.484 --> 27:45.916
Savage's house.

27:45.918 --> 27:48.386
All right, we need to
proceed on two fronts:

27:48.388 --> 27:51.422
locate Jefferson and make
an all-out assault on Savage.

27:51.424 --> 27:54.358
A full-on attack only
plays to Savage's strengths.

27:54.360 --> 27:55.367
If we want to get him...

27:55.369 --> 27:57.862
We need to target his weaknesses.

27:57.864 --> 28:01.032
Sadly, very few come to mind.

28:01.034 --> 28:03.267
I can think of one.

28:03.269 --> 28:05.202
Me.

28:05.204 --> 28:07.605
He wants me, and he always has.

28:07.607 --> 28:10.174
So if I can get close
enough to him, then...

28:10.176 --> 28:11.876
Then he'll kill you.

28:11.878 --> 28:14.612
Thank you for the vote of confidence,

28:14.614 --> 28:16.180
but I don't need your protection.

28:16.182 --> 28:18.315
There's no reason to go alone.

28:18.317 --> 28:20.217
We're part of a team for a reason.

28:20.219 --> 28:22.520
Yes, and the team seems comfortable

28:22.522 --> 28:23.821
with me doing this,

28:23.823 --> 28:25.756
so that makes it about you and me.

28:25.758 --> 28:32.283
<i>♪
♪</i>

28:32.285 --> 28:34.632
- Any updates?
- We're making progress.

28:34.634 --> 28:37.201
In the meantime, we need to
get ready to back Kendra up.

28:37.203 --> 28:39.904
She's going into the asylum
to meet Savage tonight.

28:39.906 --> 28:43.407
Another opportunity for
you to see Nurse Carlisle.

28:43.409 --> 28:46.577
Yeah, and apologize.

28:47.880 --> 28:49.580
I warned you, Ms. Lance.

28:49.582 --> 28:52.216
Rushing a repressed woman from the 1950s

28:52.218 --> 28:54.719
into the freewheeling sexual mores

28:54.721 --> 28:56.053
of the 21st century...

28:56.055 --> 28:58.923
Actually, I was the one who freaked out.

28:58.925 --> 28:59.991
Oh.

28:59.993 --> 29:02.893
Ever since I got brought back to life,

29:02.895 --> 29:05.029
I haven't really... [sighs]

29:05.031 --> 29:07.665
Experienced much in the way of feelings.

29:07.667 --> 29:10.793
And then when Lindsey kissed me...

29:10.795 --> 29:12.870
It was like you were being kissed

29:12.872 --> 29:15.339
for the first time.

29:15.341 --> 29:16.527
How romantic.

29:16.529 --> 29:19.276
It was more like terrifying.

29:19.278 --> 29:21.746
That's the thing that sucks about feelings

29:21.748 --> 29:23.714
is, you realize how much

29:23.716 --> 29:25.983
you can hurt someone

29:25.985 --> 29:29.487
or... get hurt.

29:29.489 --> 29:31.722
- Ah.
- Wakey, wakey.

29:31.724 --> 29:33.997
[groans]

29:33.999 --> 29:35.149
Ah.

29:35.151 --> 29:36.761
Do the words "police brutality"

29:36.763 --> 29:38.095
mean anything to you?

29:38.097 --> 29:39.563
You think this is brutal?

29:39.565 --> 29:40.898
You'll be begging for me

29:40.900 --> 29:43.134
after he gets through with you.

29:43.136 --> 29:44.435
That's enough, Sheriff.

29:44.437 --> 29:46.804
Thank you. Leave us be.

29:46.806 --> 29:49.039
This young man and I

29:49.041 --> 29:51.075
have a lot to discuss.

29:51.077 --> 29:53.911
Forgive my friend for his ignorance.

29:53.913 --> 29:56.947
You will learn that I'm
much more enlightened.

29:56.949 --> 29:59.450
Well, I'll take racist over crazy any day.

29:59.452 --> 30:01.185
Oh, I would hardly describe

30:01.187 --> 30:04.755
what I'm doing here as... as "crazy."

30:04.757 --> 30:06.557
Therapy is nothing more

30:06.559 --> 30:08.893
than a process of self-discovery.

30:08.895 --> 30:13.597
You're about to experience
an extraterrestrial power.

30:13.599 --> 30:15.432
Shall we begin?

30:15.434 --> 30:18.569
[grunting]

30:19.971 --> 30:23.507
Shh, shh.

30:23.509 --> 30:25.042
Ah!

30:25.044 --> 30:26.477
Ah!

30:26.479 --> 30:31.248
<i>♪
♪</i>

30:31.250 --> 30:33.450
[shrieking]

30:36.593 --> 30:39.309
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

30:39.311 --> 30:43.084
[shrieking]

30:43.086 --> 30:45.386
What a piece of work is man.

30:45.388 --> 30:47.188
[shrieking]

30:47.190 --> 30:49.123
When I was exposed to a meteorite,

30:49.125 --> 30:52.026
I was blessed with eternal life,

30:52.028 --> 30:53.828
immortality.

30:53.830 --> 30:56.464
But sadly, the effect of this meteorite

30:56.466 --> 30:58.533
turned out quite different.

30:58.535 --> 31:00.264
[hisses]

31:00.266 --> 31:02.036
But no less advantageous.

31:02.038 --> 31:03.104
[giggles]

31:03.106 --> 31:05.273
Doc, you have a visitor.

31:08.445 --> 31:11.613
[shrieking]

31:12.582 --> 31:21.460
<i>♪
♪</i>

31:21.462 --> 31:23.721
What a pleasant surprise.

31:23.723 --> 31:26.027
Is it a surprise...

31:26.029 --> 31:28.229
or fate?

31:28.231 --> 31:30.898
We didn't get to finish our
discussion the other night.

31:30.900 --> 31:34.636
What of your square-jawed
husband, Raymond?

31:34.638 --> 31:37.548
I didn't come here to
talk about my husband,

31:37.550 --> 31:39.935
Doctor.

31:39.937 --> 31:43.036
May I?

31:43.038 --> 31:46.172
May I take your coat?

31:49.786 --> 31:51.217
<i>Make yourself comfortable.</i>

31:51.219 --> 31:52.654
Nurse?

31:52.656 --> 31:54.589
Nurse, I keep hearing voices in my head.

31:54.591 --> 31:58.059
My wife with another man,

31:58.061 --> 31:59.494
and it's driving me crazy.

31:59.496 --> 32:01.429
Well, maybe you should
learn to trust your wife

32:01.431 --> 32:03.033
a little bit more.

32:03.035 --> 32:04.732
Orderly?

32:04.734 --> 32:07.368
Show our new patient to his room.

32:07.370 --> 32:09.137
And don't hesitate to give him a sedative

32:09.139 --> 32:11.472
if he doesn't calm down.

32:11.474 --> 32:14.142
Right away, Nurse.

32:15.145 --> 32:23.250
<i>♪
♪</i>

32:23.252 --> 32:25.386
I'm sure the kid is fine.

32:25.388 --> 32:26.754
Jefferson and I, as you know,

32:26.756 --> 32:28.022
share a psychic connection,

32:28.024 --> 32:30.425
but for some inexplicable reason,

32:30.427 --> 32:32.327
I can't seem to reach him.

32:32.329 --> 32:35.029
[sighs] I've grown so
accustomed to our partnership,

32:35.031 --> 32:37.418
to suddenly be without him is disquieting.

32:37.420 --> 32:39.267
I know the feeling.

32:39.269 --> 32:43.104
<i>♪
♪</i>

32:43.106 --> 32:46.474
So have you tried psychoanalysis before?

32:46.476 --> 32:48.409
No.

32:48.411 --> 32:51.179
My husband thinks it's baloney.

32:51.181 --> 32:53.081
Oh, is that so?

32:53.083 --> 32:54.949
Well, my specialty is

32:54.951 --> 32:57.107
interpreting dreams.

32:57.109 --> 32:58.853
What do you dream, Kendra?

32:58.855 --> 33:01.539
To be honest,

33:01.541 --> 33:03.975
I've dreamt of you before...

33:03.977 --> 33:06.741
and me...

33:06.743 --> 33:08.863
together.

33:08.865 --> 33:11.299
Well, that's interesting.

33:11.301 --> 33:15.436
And what do we do in those dreams?

33:15.438 --> 33:17.238
I'm afraid you'll think me forward.

33:17.240 --> 33:19.841
Oh, but you are forward.

33:19.843 --> 33:22.844
Coming here in that dress?

33:22.846 --> 33:25.446
Perhaps you should learn
to embrace your desires

33:25.448 --> 33:28.883
so the two of us can finally be together.

33:28.885 --> 33:35.314
<i>♪
♪</i>

33:35.316 --> 33:37.191
Did you lose something?

33:37.193 --> 33:38.758
[gasps]

33:38.760 --> 33:40.194
I was wondering how long

33:40.196 --> 33:42.139
you could play out this little charade.

33:42.141 --> 33:42.964
Ah!

33:42.966 --> 33:44.298
You show up on my doorstep,

33:44.300 --> 33:46.868
and then my dagger goes missing?

33:46.870 --> 33:49.504
You must think me stupid

33:49.506 --> 33:52.440
not to suspect that
your powers had emerged.

33:52.442 --> 33:55.843
♪ ♪

33:55.845 --> 33:57.011
[groans]

33:57.013 --> 33:58.312
Well, well, well.

33:58.314 --> 34:01.549
An FBI agent moonlighting at the loony bin.

34:01.551 --> 34:02.884
I'm afraid both of you boys

34:02.886 --> 34:04.419
have some explaining to do

34:04.421 --> 34:06.387
down at the station.

34:06.389 --> 34:08.917
Who else have you brought
to the asylum tonight?

34:08.918 --> 34:11.489
No one. No one! It's just me.

34:11.492 --> 34:13.060
I hope you're better at lying

34:13.062 --> 34:16.063
in your next life.

34:16.065 --> 34:17.364
[intercom buzzes]

34:17.367 --> 34:19.132
[alarm ringing]

34:19.135 --> 34:20.268
[cawing]

34:20.270 --> 34:21.505
Oh, boy.

34:21.507 --> 34:23.704
Just when you think you've seen everything.

34:23.706 --> 34:25.406
[shrieking]

34:25.408 --> 34:26.706
[whooshing]

34:30.380 --> 34:33.014
Guess those missing kids
are no longer missing.

34:33.016 --> 34:34.315
<i>[people screaming]</i>

34:34.317 --> 34:36.516
What have you done? Ah!

34:36.518 --> 34:38.920
I released my test subjects.

34:38.922 --> 34:42.190
The energy from the
meteorite has changed them.

34:42.192 --> 34:46.092
I set out to build an
army as powerful as you.

34:46.094 --> 34:48.896
Pity they didn't turn
out nearly as beautiful.

34:48.898 --> 34:51.331
[both grunting]

34:51.333 --> 34:56.804
<i>♪
♪</i>

34:56.806 --> 34:59.607
[guttural growling]

35:00.777 --> 35:03.177
Oh, my God.

35:03.179 --> 35:06.113
It's Jefferson.

35:06.115 --> 35:08.149
Jefferson, it's... it's us!

35:08.151 --> 35:10.117
[snarls]

35:10.119 --> 35:13.788
[shrieking]

35:13.790 --> 35:16.457
Jax, don't make me do this.

35:16.459 --> 35:19.994
<i>♪
♪</i>

35:19.996 --> 35:23.931
[shrieking]

35:23.933 --> 35:27.568
[whooshing]

35:27.570 --> 35:28.803
[roars]

35:28.805 --> 35:31.939
<i>♪
♪</i>

35:31.941 --> 35:33.140
Ah!

35:34.777 --> 35:36.010
I'll deal with this lot.

35:36.012 --> 35:37.645
Find Kendra now.

35:37.647 --> 35:39.080
[growling]

35:39.082 --> 35:41.015
[people screaming]

35:41.017 --> 35:42.283
[roaring]

35:42.285 --> 35:44.318
[screams]

35:44.320 --> 35:45.219
[shrieks]

35:45.221 --> 35:53.461
<i>♪
♪</i>

35:57.634 --> 35:59.400
[gasps]

36:02.505 --> 36:05.439
I can explain. Just not now.

36:05.441 --> 36:13.899
<i>♪
♪</i>

36:13.901 --> 36:15.583
Perhaps it will turn out better

36:15.585 --> 36:17.518
in our next life, my love.

36:17.520 --> 36:20.555
[whooshing]

36:20.557 --> 36:23.424
Are you okay?

36:23.426 --> 36:25.660
<i>♪
♪</i>

36:25.662 --> 36:29.063
[shrieking]

36:29.065 --> 36:38.172
<i>♪
♪</i>

36:38.174 --> 36:40.745
It's time to go.

36:40.747 --> 36:42.532
Not without Jefferson.

36:42.534 --> 36:44.946
Or whatever's left of him.

36:48.953 --> 36:50.708
Gideon was able to help me devise

36:50.710 --> 36:52.222
a gene therapy that will hopefully

36:52.224 --> 36:54.354
restore Jefferson and those at the asylum

36:54.356 --> 36:55.622
to their former selves.

36:55.624 --> 36:57.290
If genome bonding occurs,

36:57.292 --> 36:58.968
we should know right away.

36:58.970 --> 37:00.682
Course, we would never have
had the slightest chance

37:00.684 --> 37:02.529
of saving him were it not for you.

37:02.531 --> 37:04.097
Let's not get sentimental.

37:04.099 --> 37:05.565
Another minute, and things might have

37:05.567 --> 37:07.734
gone down very differently.

37:07.736 --> 37:10.637
Despite your bravado, Mr. Snart,

37:10.639 --> 37:12.239
the actions that I witnessed last night

37:12.241 --> 37:14.441
were nothing short of heroic.

37:14.443 --> 37:16.309
<i>[computer beeping]</i>

37:16.311 --> 37:19.246
<i>[soft music]</i>

37:19.248 --> 37:22.949
<i>♪
♪</i>

37:22.951 --> 37:24.451
It's working.

37:24.453 --> 37:31.391
<i>♪
♪</i>

37:31.393 --> 37:33.293
Hey.

37:33.295 --> 37:35.428
How are our friends doing over in Hall H?

37:35.430 --> 37:37.330
Whatever Dr. Stein gave those creatures

37:37.332 --> 37:38.865
seemed to have worked.

37:38.867 --> 37:40.267
They're back to normal.

37:43.526 --> 37:45.539
And you?

37:45.541 --> 37:49.876
Not sure if I'm ever gonna
get fully back to normal.

37:49.878 --> 37:52.813
Good.

37:52.815 --> 38:00.620
<i>♪
♪</i>

38:00.622 --> 38:02.389
Thank you...

38:02.391 --> 38:04.291
for rescuing me.

38:04.293 --> 38:05.625
Well, you rescued me first,

38:05.627 --> 38:09.830
so now we're even.

38:09.832 --> 38:11.832
You have to go, don't you?

38:11.834 --> 38:14.668
- [sighs]
- I get it.

38:14.670 --> 38:17.404
Should've known better
than to fall for a ninja.

38:17.406 --> 38:20.607
[both chuckle]

38:22.110 --> 38:25.078
Who knows? Maybe I'll be back one day.

38:25.080 --> 38:26.780
And if so...

38:26.782 --> 38:28.315
You know where to find me.

38:28.317 --> 38:33.887
<i>♪
♪</i>

38:33.889 --> 38:36.456
So I felt bad about trashing your dad's.

38:36.458 --> 38:39.159
I thought this might make up for it.

38:39.161 --> 38:40.260
You bought me a car?

38:40.262 --> 38:41.595
I souped it up too.

38:41.597 --> 38:43.597
In case of future monster attacks.

38:43.599 --> 38:45.932
[both laugh]

38:45.934 --> 38:48.435
I wish you didn't have to go.

38:48.437 --> 38:50.303
I don't belong here.

38:50.305 --> 38:52.105
And neither do you.

38:52.107 --> 38:54.307
Promise me you'll get out of this town.

38:54.309 --> 38:56.343
The both of you.

38:56.345 --> 38:58.211
Tommy!

38:58.213 --> 39:00.080
It's a great big world out there, Betty.

39:00.082 --> 39:02.249
And it's changing fast.

39:02.251 --> 39:05.252
Maybe we'll catch up
down the road somewhere.

39:05.254 --> 39:11.925
<i>♪
♪</i>

39:11.927 --> 39:14.127
Hey. I was just packing up.

39:14.129 --> 39:15.620
I thought you were back at the Waverider.

39:15.622 --> 39:17.797
I just forgot something.

39:17.799 --> 39:20.033
I forgot to say I'm sorry.

39:20.035 --> 39:22.302
Look, I was wrong to think that I could

39:22.304 --> 39:24.037
actually end Savage by myself.

39:24.039 --> 39:27.007
Whoa. Whoa, whoa, whoa. Just slow down.

39:27.009 --> 39:28.675
I made a mistake too.

39:28.677 --> 39:30.310
I got so caught up playing house

39:30.312 --> 39:34.047
that I forgot about
why we were really here.

39:34.049 --> 39:37.517
And you will end Savage someday.

39:37.519 --> 39:38.685
I guess the last thing

39:38.687 --> 39:40.186
a 4,000-year-old
demigoddess needs

39:40.188 --> 39:43.323
is an overprotective husband.

39:43.325 --> 39:47.060
What she needs is a partner.

39:47.062 --> 39:49.696
What do you say?

39:52.668 --> 39:53.867
Partner.

39:53.869 --> 40:01.708
<i>♪
♪</i>

40:04.513 --> 40:06.546
Well, look who's up and around.

40:06.548 --> 40:09.749
Mm, yeah.

40:09.751 --> 40:12.185
I guess I owe you an apology.

40:12.187 --> 40:15.355
Grey told me about what
happened back at the asylum.

40:15.357 --> 40:18.525
You had the chance to
kill me, and you didn't.

40:18.527 --> 40:20.894
After last night, I know
enough about being a monster

40:20.896 --> 40:22.162
to know that you're not one.

40:22.164 --> 40:25.865
Stop. I'm getting misty-eyed.

40:25.867 --> 40:28.301
I just want you to know...

40:28.303 --> 40:30.540
about what happened with Rory?

40:30.542 --> 40:32.572
I get it.

40:32.574 --> 40:34.107
You were protecting us.

40:34.109 --> 40:35.176
And that doesn't make you a murderer.

40:35.178 --> 40:37.243
It makes you a part of this team.

40:37.245 --> 40:38.812
Jefferson, you should be resting.

40:38.814 --> 40:40.947
Aw, man, I'm... I'm done laying around.

40:40.949 --> 40:42.454
I just want to get the
hell out of Mayberry.

40:42.456 --> 40:44.651
Agreed... we're still waiting on Sara

40:44.653 --> 40:46.853
and the two lovebirds to get back.

40:46.855 --> 40:50.413
Seems they've taken quite a shine to 1958.

40:50.415 --> 40:51.992
<i>[explosion]</i>

40:51.994 --> 40:53.393
What on earth?

40:53.395 --> 40:55.528
Gideon?

40:55.530 --> 40:57.122
Not this guy again.

40:57.124 --> 40:59.380
<i>Captain, Chronos has
breached the starboard hatch.</i>

40:59.382 --> 40:59.993
How is that possible?

40:59.995 --> 41:01.298
Clearly, he's received some new toys

41:01.300 --> 41:03.590
from his Time Master friends
since our last encounter.

41:03.592 --> 41:06.526
Gideon, seal the bulkheads
from here until...

41:07.843 --> 41:10.777
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:10.779 --> 41:14.080
<i>♪
♪</i>

41:14.082 --> 41:15.182
Grey, come on! Let's do this!

41:15.184 --> 41:16.716
If we merge on the Waverider,

41:16.718 --> 41:18.084
we could destroy the entire ship!

41:18.086 --> 41:19.386
Um, are you not paying attention

41:19.388 --> 41:21.755
to what Chronos is doing?

41:21.757 --> 41:23.123
Fall back!

41:23.125 --> 41:24.657
Get to the jump ship!

41:24.659 --> 41:29.496
<i>♪
♪</i>

41:29.498 --> 41:30.856
1958's swell and all,

41:30.858 --> 41:33.493
but I miss the Internet...

41:33.495 --> 41:36.102
and cell phones.

41:38.640 --> 41:40.601
Uh...

41:40.603 --> 41:42.490
what are they doing?

41:42.492 --> 41:43.843
- Hey.
- Hey!

41:43.845 --> 41:48.214
<i>♪
♪</i>

41:48.216 --> 41:50.917
Where did they go?

41:50.919 --> 41:52.619
Better question:

41:52.621 --> 41:54.587
why did they leave us?

41:54.589 --> 41:58.858
<i>♪
♪</i>

